1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:02,879
(Previously) And the director
of this year's stage play is…

2
00:00:02,880 --> 00:00:03,920
Jack!

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:07,159
I'm making Romeo &amp; Romeo.

4
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:08,160
I will retell the story.

5
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:09,280
As for the lead actors…

6
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:10,520
we're holding auditions.

7
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:13,320
Oh, hey, are you interested
in joining our faculty play?

8
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,160
Me?

9
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:15,440
You'll get paid too.

10
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:16,760
I will?

11
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:18,880
Shit!
Shit! I'm sorry.

12
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,840
How should I make it up to you?

13
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,080
Don't worry.

14
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,840
You will surely get the chance to.

15
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:26,519
There's no point in holding auditions.

16
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:29,080
The Romeo role is mine. No question.

17
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,360
Your method won't work.

18
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,160
We won't know…

19
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,320
unless we try. Right?

20
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:53,920
Hey.

21
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:56,680
We barely get any time together,

22
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,400
yet you keep staring at
that book instead of my face.

23
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:03,560
Hey.

24
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:04,880
Dean!

25
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:06,360
I was just about to get an idea.

26
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:07,600
What kind of idea?

27
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:10,519
No matter how many times you read it,
the ending never changes.

28
00:01:10,520 --> 00:01:13,200
Romeo and Juliet still die.

29
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:16,240
No.

30
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:19,000
If you were Juliet, what would you do?

31
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,120
If I were Juliet?

32
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:28,360
If anyone tried to stand
between us, I'd fight.

33
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:30,880
Until my last breath.

34
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,120
What about you?

35
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:36,280
Would you fight for me?

36
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:39,960
I guess so.

37
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,920
And if I couldn't win,
I'd just take you and run.

38
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Sounds good?

39
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,760
Fine. No problem with that.

40
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:51,320
Hey.

41
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,840
I want to reinterpret Romeo and Juliet.

42
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:58,600
Make it about two men

43
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:02,400
from families divided by their beliefs.

44
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:06,760
But this time, they have a happy ending,
where they get to stay together.

45
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:07,840
What do you think?

46
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,520
You're right.

47
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:13,000
Why can't people in love be together?

48
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:23,960
A project this good,
you have to let me play.

49
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:25,960
Mm.

50
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:29,240
I'll direct. You'll act.

51
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,840
You're both my boyfriend
and my favorite actor.

52
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,520
Hm?

53
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:44,760
Here.

54
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,960
What's this?

55
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,320
Your anniversary gift.

56
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,280
And you're just handing it to me like this?

57
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,760
Yes. Just like this.

58
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,600
Happy first anniversary.

59
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,640
Let me put it on you.

60
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,320
Thanks a lot.

61
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,000
Hey, Dean.

62
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:28,840
What are you doing?
People can see.

63
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,120
Are you scared they will?

64
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,280
What are you doing now?

65
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,639
Hey, stop it.

66
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,160
Dean, I said stop.

67
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:43,880
That's enough.

68
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,520
Oh, come on.

69
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:14,700
"Only Friends: Dream On"
(Episode 2)

70
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,640
Can't we cuddle a little longer?

71
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,680
No.

72
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,480
I have a casting to
get to. I need to hurry.

73
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,720
Why do you still need to cast?

74
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,280
You already had your Romeo.

75
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:04,920
Many times.

76
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,600
I mean the other one.

77
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:14,000
For the Romeo you're aiming for,
I haven't decided yet.

78
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,560
I gave you my body.
Am I really getting nothing in return?

79
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,960
We're just exes hooking up.

80
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,440
No feelings involved.

81
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,200
How cruel.

82
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,360
Hey.

83
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:39,640
What are you doing?

84
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,960
You can't post that, Dean.

85
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,800
It was just for me.

86
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,560
Why?

87
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,800
Why don't you unblock me?

88
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,800
Then you'll know whether I post it or not.

89
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,960
I'm not posting it.
I was just messing with him.

90
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:10,240
Why do you care what other people think?

91
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:13,840
Isn't what we feel for each other enough?

92
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,280
Or are you not feeling it?

93
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,280
Cut.

94
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,520
Ah… Arnold.

95
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,440
Have you ever hit on someone before?

96
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,520
Hit on someone?

97
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,040
I have, kind of.

98
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:32,160
But most of the time, people approach me.

99
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,880
Ah, I see.

100
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:39,400
How about you forget the script this time
and improvise for me?

101
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,760
Timmy, help him.

102
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:43,960
Are you crazy?

103
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,480
I can't act.

104
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,440
I'll make a fool of myself. No way.

105
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:51,360
Tua, don't laugh.

106
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:52,960
Go help Arnold with the improvisation.

107
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:53,360
What?
Go on.

108
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,040
- Me?
- Yes.

109
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,080
Give me the script.
- Hey.
- Just go.

110
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,200
- For real?
- Yes.

111
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,480
You've got this, buddy.

112
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,760
Okay.

113
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,160
This time.

114
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:13,680
You can touch his arms, hold his hands.
Do anything to make him melt.

115
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,320
Are you serious?

116
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,680
Yes, I am.

117
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,520
Whenever you're ready, Arnold.

118
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,240
Tua.

119
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,920
How long have we known each other?

120
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,560
Three years.

121
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,480
We're going into our fourth this year.

122
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,000
Mm.

123
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:46,200
Have you ever counted how many times
you've sat behind me on my bike?

124
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,439
Who would even count that?

125
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,440
42 times.

126
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,680
Huh?

127
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,120
You counted?

128
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,160
From a guy who forgets his own birthday?

129
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,680
Because it's you. That's why I remember.

130
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:08,280
And if you look closely, you'll see
I've never let anyone else ride with me.

131
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,600
Only you.

132
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:15,480
At first, I hesitated about telling you.

133
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,040
But we're graduating soon.

134
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,280
I don't want to miss this chance.

135
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,640
I like you, Tua.

136
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,000
What about you?

137
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,040
How do you feel about me?

138
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Uh…

139
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,760
I…

140
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:49,680
Cut!

141
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,600
Was that okay?

142
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,520
I don't think Jack knows.

143
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,960
Maybe it's just a coincidence.

144
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,520
I hope I didn't blush so
much that people noticed.

145
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:15,680
I wasn't blushing.

146
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:18,000
I just felt ticklish, having
to confess to my friend.

147
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,480
Tua should understand.

148
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:23,720
Honestly, I'm more nervous
about the audition results.

149
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:27,000
I've got my two Romeos.

150
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,080
All right, everyone. Listen up.

151
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:37,640
This is the moment
we've all been waiting for.

152
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:40,520
The audition results for our faculty play.

153
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:49,520
The first Romeo goes to…

154
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,040
Arnold!

155
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:02,840
Hey!
You did it.

156
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,000
Thank you so much, Tua.

157
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,000
Congratulations.
Thanks.

158
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:11,280
And the other Romeo is…

159
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:15,640
Dean!

160
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:38,880
Raffy.

161
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,440
It's okay.

162
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,320
I can give you a friend role instead.

163
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,600
I'm sorry, Jack.

164
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:50,480
I think you should find
someone else for the part.

165
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:54,600
I'll help out behind the scenes instead.

166
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,280
Gosh.

167
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:03,360
The play hasn't even started,
and someone's already quitting.

168
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:08,080
Which god do I need to
pray to for this play to survive?

169
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,520
Dang it.

170
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:37,760
If you're here to get under
my skin, I'm not in the mood.

171
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:43,880
You're this worked up
over not getting the role?

172
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,200
Isn't being part of the play good enough?

173
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,280
You don't have to quit.

174
00:12:47,281 --> 00:12:50,040
I want the lead, not some supporting role.

175
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:56,920
Or you're really this furious
because you won't get to be near Jack.

176
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:02,160
I'm furious right now because I'm near you.

177
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:03,960
Ooh.

178
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:15,680
Actually, I came because
we need to go buy a new DJ controller.

179
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,560
You spilled a drink all over mine.

180
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,200
Why do I have to go?

181
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,640
Just tell me the price. I'll
transfer the money right now.

182
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:28,000
You wasted my time that day.
Today's your turn to waste yours.

183
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:31,120
Or did you not mean what you said?

184
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:34,320
You don't actually want
to take responsibility.

185
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:38,880
What do you want, then?

186
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:45,760
How about a swim race?

187
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:48,240
First to finish three laps wins.

188
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:52,840
And if I win, you come with me.

189
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:57,640
And if I win?

190
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,600
Not happening.

191
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,240
Movie ticket, please.

192
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,040
How many?
Two, please.

193
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,239
Two for 600 baht. Please scan here.

194
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,240
Sure.

195
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:51,960
All done.

196
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,080
Did you follow me?

197
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,480
I did not.

198
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:11,120
I wanted to watch La La Land, too.

199
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,320
Besides,

200
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:17,440
this is our favorite movie, right?

201
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,760
Thank you for choosing me.

202
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,800
I chose you because of your talent.

203
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,760
It had nothing to do with
the sex the other day.

204
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,520
Okay, Jack.

205
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:43,800
I'll try to believe you.

206
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:49,600
If I chose based on sex,
I wouldn't have just two Romeos.

207
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,600
Hey, Jack.

208
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:53,880
Are you here to see...
I came alone

209
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,080
and ran into a friend.

210
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,560
Are you here alone, Ice?

211
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:00,920
Mm.

212
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,560
Should we… watch it together?

213
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:06,720
And tonight…

214
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:09,680
let's catch up.

215
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,440
Who's that?

216
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,640
Another one of my Romeos.

217
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,240
I'll see you inside.

218
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,480
One cup of cocoa, please.

219
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:44,720
Ice, right?

220
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,320
Yes.

221
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,840
I'm Dean. A friend of Jack's.

222
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:49,600
Do you come here often?

223
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:50,880
Not really.

224
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:53,720
I just love this movie,
so I'm here for a rewatch.

225
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,160
I love this movie too.

226
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,560
But I like to watch it here.

227
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,760
It gives better vibes
than watching at home.

228
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,200
Here's your cocoa.

229
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,240
Thank you.

230
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:06,720
I'll see you inside then.

231
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,120
Okay.

232
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,200
Shit!

233
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:13,480
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

234
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:14,960
I'm sorry.
That's enough!

235
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:20,840
Damn it.

236
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:28,720
If I don't get what I want,

237
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,160
nobody does.

238
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,800
Hey.

239
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,120
This seat is taken.

240
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,560
No, it isn't.

241
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,160
I don't see anyone sitting here.

242
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,480
He's coming.

243
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:58,560
He's not.

244
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:00,800
I saw him leave.

245
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:04,200
I guess he had an emergency.

246
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:09,600
You don't have to look.

247
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,240
Just watch the movie.

248
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:17,080
A favorite movie should
be seen with a favorite ex.

249
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,880
Movie time.

250
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,040
What's that face?

251
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,600
Nothing. I'm just a little on edge.

252
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:51,120
I don't know if I'll fit in
with everyone in the play.

253
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,720
Don't worry. They're super chill.

254
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,640
Just be ready to answer one question.

255
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,680
I'm sure they'll ask where
your name comes from.

256
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:06,400
“My dad loves The Terminator.”

257
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:09,040
“He's a huge fan of Arnold Schwarzenegger.”

258
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:10,480
“That's how I got this name.”

259
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:11,720
Tua, stop it.

260
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:13,599
“Talk to the hand.”

261
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:14,160
Quit that.

262
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,200
“I'll be back.”

263
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,400
I'm poking your eyes out.

264
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:19,600
I'm just teasing.

265
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:23,120
But there's one person. Jack.

266
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:24,600
He's a bit strict.

267
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:27,480
Just be patient and follow his lead.

268
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:29,160
Mm.

269
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,440
Jack also told me…

270
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,320
there are scenes where I
have to hug and kiss Dean.

271
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:37,560
Why?

272
00:19:38,095 --> 00:19:40,640
Are you worried about kissing a guy?

273
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:47,560
No. I have no problem kissing a guy.

274
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,440
But I've never kissed
someone I'm not close to.

275
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,640
Come on.

276
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:57,800
You'll get closer after the workshops.

277
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,440
Speaking of kissing,

278
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,600
it reminds me of my first kiss.

279
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:08,600
Mine was back in junior high.

280
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,880
It was with a girl from a lower grade.

281
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:13,600
But it didn't turn into anything.

282
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,560
What about you?

283
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:22,760
Hm?

284
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:25,000
When was your first kiss? Hm?

285
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:28,520
Mine was…

286
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,640
a little late.

287
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:32,080
It's just last year.

288
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:33,160
Huh?

289
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:34,560
Last year?

290
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,600
Hey, wait!

291
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,520
Where have I been? How did I not know this?

292
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:43,080
Tell me. Who was it?

293
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,600
Just some asshole.

294
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,920
That's why I don't want to remember.

295
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:55,040
Shit.

296
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:56,240
I'm sorry.

297
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:58,360
I shouldn't have asked, right?

298
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:02,760
Forget it. It was a long time ago.

299
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,120
I'm okay now.

300
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:09,800
Hey, Dean.

301
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:10,600
Sorry.

302
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,960
I thought no one was home.

303
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:15,360
Am I invading?

304
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,040
I can leave.

305
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,720
Hey, it's fine.

306
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,680
This is Tua's place, after all.

307
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,440
I'm just his housemate.

308
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:26,160
If he's okay with it, I am too.

309
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:30,680
Have a seat. Eat with us.

310
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:33,040
So you two can get to know each other.

311
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,680
Wow, this looks amazing.

312
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,400
You made so much.

313
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:42,200
Arnold's worried about the love scenes
you two have together.

314
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:44,000
Tua!

315
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,160
Talk to him.

316
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,160
No worries.

317
00:21:47,353 --> 00:21:49,713
We'll get used to each
other after the workshops.

318
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Wow, this is a lot.

319
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,560
Are you Ranchalee's son?

320
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:15,760
Right?

321
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:17,680
I'm Raffy.

322
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:19,040
Okay, Little Raffy.

323
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:21,560
Can I take photos with you?

324
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:24,999
I'm your mom's biggest fan.

325
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:28,160
I've loved her since Love
Beneath the Sea of Stars.

326
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,760
Let's take photos.

327
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:33,280
One more, please.

328
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:35,920
I have a name.

329
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:38,839
But people keep calling me Ranchalee's son

330
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:39,840
or Little Raf.

331
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,040
Thank you.

332
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,239
Just pick whatever you like.

333
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:48,599
I'll give you a special discount.

334
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,600
Take your time.

335
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:54,600
How cool.

336
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:06,040
Just make it quick so we can leave.

337
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:10,040
Help me choose.

338
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:11,200
What? No.

339
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,960
It's your gear. You choose.

340
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,360
Oh, come on. Just pick one.

341
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:19,760
Which one would you
choose between these two?

342
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:22,960
Go with the one that catches your eye.

343
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:25,400
You're such a pain.

344
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:35,920
Here.

345
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:37,280
Let's go with this one.

346
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:38,120
This one?

347
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,320
Mm.

348
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:40,640
Whoa.

349
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,200
Nice taste.

350
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,200
Can I try this one?

351
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,240
Of course.

352
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,120
All you do is act cool.

353
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:19,120
Who knew you were actually good?

354
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,800
GOT TIME? COME SEE ME AT THE UNI.

355
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:29,280
LET'S TALK. JUST THE TWO OF US.

356
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,720
Hey, you want this controller, right?

357
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,920
Excuse me. I'll pay by card.

358
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,679
Hey, I'm not even sure yet.

359
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:37,200
Here.
Just a moment, please.

360
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,240
I gotta run.

361
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:41,360
What's the rush?

362
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,000
None of your business.

363
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:44,760
I'm buying this for you. We're even now.

364
00:24:45,040 --> 00:24:46,440
Get my card for me.

365
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:46,960
What?

366
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,000
Bye.

367
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:49,400
Hey!

368
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,520
Say what you want.

369
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,640
Are you going to yell at me for quitting?

370
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,560
Why would I yell at you?

371
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,920
I just want you to
reconsider the supporting role.

372
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:29,040
That friend role you want me to play

373
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:31,760
could be played by anyone.

374
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:35,120
Hey. Not just anyone.

375
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:38,960
No character in my play is unimportant.

376
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:46,520
Didn't you say you wanted to
act in something I direct?

377
00:25:49,906 --> 00:25:53,906
This might be the last chance
we get to work together.

378
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,480
Please,

379
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:01,800
Raffy.

380
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:05,280
Well…

381
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:08,160
If you want me to do it that bad,

382
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:11,520
I'll do it.

383
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,400
Holy shit.

384
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,200
Thank you, Raffy.

385
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:22,393
I actually prepared to
pester you some more.

386
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:26,000
I thought I'd have to beg.

387
00:26:28,553 --> 00:26:29,553
Well…

388
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:32,600
You're the one who asked.

389
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:34,960
Here.

390
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:37,600
The new script I edited just for you.

391
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:39,280
Take a look.

392
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:42,840
This is the first act.

393
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,280
Jack was clearly pleading.

394
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:54,720
With that kind of effort,
of course I went back.

395
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:57,920
Jack.

396
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:02,040
Why did you include Raffy in this project?

397
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:03,840
Was there really no one else?

398
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,360
Dean, be professional.

399
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:10,240
I think Raffy suits that role.

400
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:11,600
Suits?

401
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,120
You never change.

402
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,680
You're always casting the people you like.

403
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:17,280
Why?

404
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,640
Are you jealous?

405
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:23,400
Dean, learn to separate things.

406
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,920
Work is work. Personal
matters are personal..

407
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,359
Hey, sorry.

408
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:29,360
Am I interrupting, Jack?

409
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:32,720
No.

410
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:33,880
What is it?

411
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:37,200
I need to tell you something.

412
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:42,840
Go on.

413
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:45,760
I'm dropping out to focus on my band.

414
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,160
We've been getting busier,

415
00:27:48,593 --> 00:27:50,193
and I need to give it my full attention.

416
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:53,920
But Billy, this is your final year.

417
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,320
It was a hard decision.

418
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,320
But the opportunity is
here. I have to seize it.

419
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:01,560
Come on now.

420
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,280
I'll come watch the play, alright.

421
00:28:03,960 --> 00:28:04,960
See you then.

422
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:05,560
See you, Dean.

423
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:06,840
See you.

424
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:19,800
Why are you so tense?

425
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,600
Of course I am.

426
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:25,480
I picked the best people for this project.

427
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,160
What else can you do?

428
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,480
Billy wants to chase his dreams.

429
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,840
You'll find someone else.

430
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:39,520
Your little brother Rome.

431
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:42,600
He's good. And he has good taste.

432
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:44,560
He's not my little brother.

433
00:28:45,133 --> 00:28:47,693
Besides, I don't want to work with him.

434
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,800
I don't want any trouble.

435
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:51,880
Okay.

436
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:56,640
But you just told me to
separate work from personal matters.

437
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:01,840
If you don't pick Rome just because
he's your mom's new boyfriend's son,

438
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,080
then you're not separating
work from personal matters either.

439
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:20,520
Hello.

440
00:29:20,521 --> 00:29:22,519
Hey, you came home today.

441
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:23,680
Did you forget something?

442
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,240
Where's that jerk Rome?

443
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:28,440
Call your brother properly.

444
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:31,320
How many times do I have to tell you?
We're family now.

445
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:35,560
Where is Rome, Mom?

446
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:40,560
If he's not out,
he's always in his room, DJing.

447
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:56,080
My oh my.

448
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:57,920
You still remember the way home, huh?

449
00:29:58,360 --> 00:30:00,320
I thought you were too busy with your play.

450
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:04,280
I came because of the play.

451
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:06,160
I need your help.

452
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,880
Is my capable big bro
really asking me for help?

453
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:14,440
So you're not helping?

454
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,280
Fine. I'll leave.

455
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,240
Wait, wait.

456
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,040
Tell me what it is.

457
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,000
Maybe I can.

458
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,160
Can you…

459
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:32,160
do sound for my play?

460
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,800
Have you even seen
my work before asking for my help?

461
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:39,120
Dean recommended you.

462
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,880
So I checked out your channel a bit.

463
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:45,720
Your style can fit the play.

464
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,280
You're back with Dean?

465
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,320
Stay out of it.

466
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:56,920
Are you helping or not?

467
00:30:58,159 --> 00:31:00,559
Fine. I'll do it.

468
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:02,760
But let me make one thing clear.

469
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:05,640
Even if you're the director,
don't boss me around.

470
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:08,520
You get it, right?
Artists need freedom to work.

471
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:10,840
Mm.

472
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:16,760
No problem.

473
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:19,400
Now people will finally see
how talented I am.

474
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:21,760
I just didn't have a choice.

475
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:30,400
I never knew there was
a pre-production party for stage plays.

476
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:34,400
It's just our excuse to drink.

477
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:36,920
What about the others?

478
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:37,960
Are they coming?

479
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,559
Jack and Dean are out to buy wine.

480
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,000
Timmy is always late.

481
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,000
The rest are on their way.

482
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:45,600
Here. The vegetables are washed.

483
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:47,240
Just tell me what else to do.

484
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,160
Can you help me slice the meat?

485
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:52,600
Of course.

486
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,640
Let me.

487
00:32:08,880 --> 00:32:09,880
Hey.

488
00:32:13,760 --> 00:32:14,960
It's your phone grip.

489
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:18,360
When people ask about your name,
just point to it.

490
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:19,880
You won't have to explain anymore.

491
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:22,919
No freaking way, Tua.

492
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:23,920
It's cute.

493
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:25,320
The Terminator?

494
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,600
Where did you get it?

495
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:29,520
Thank you.

496
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:33,080
Looks like you, huh?

497
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:34,400
Stick it on my phone?

498
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,000
Mhm.

499
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,000
“I'm the Terminator.”

500
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:43,000
“I… will be back.”

501
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:44,720
Nice impression.

502
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:46,480
My whole body is made of steel.

503
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:49,800
Now you're teasing yourself?

504
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:19,800
What's up, big actress's son?

505
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:21,640
You again?

506
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:23,200
Did you follow me here?

507
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:25,519
I took you to buy that new controller.
What else do you want?

508
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,520
Don't flatter yourself.

509
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:28,200
I'm here for the party too.

510
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:29,840
What?

511
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:32,000
Why?

512
00:33:32,840 --> 00:33:34,440
I'm part of the production now.

513
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,200
Jack asked me to run the sound.

514
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:39,040
From now on,
we'll be seeing each other a lot.

515
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:49,640
♪ When we get too close, too real ♪

516
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:53,000
♪ Tell me if you dare ♪

517
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:55,360
♪ If you want to be just friends ♪

518
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:58,320
♪ Stay in that lane ♪

519
00:33:58,440 --> 00:33:59,600
Gosh, Timmy.

520
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,919
Do you have to turn into
a singer every time you're drunk?

521
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:02,920
What?

522
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:04,319
Are you saying I'm not good?

523
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:04,920
Cheers. Come on.

524
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:06,160
Of course.

525
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:10,120
Wow!

526
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,560
Here they come.

527
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,520
Took you guys long enough.

528
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,200
I thought you murdered each other.

529
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:19,320
Who told you that? We're on good terms.

530
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:23,440
The director and his
favorite actor are back.

531
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:25,080
Wow!

532
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:29,200
What are you all looking at?

533
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:30,720
Stop teasing.

534
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:34,640
Dean and I are just coworkers,
like the rest of you.

535
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,080
Sure.

536
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:37,240
Okay?

537
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:43,920
Since everyone's here,
why don't you say something, Jack?

538
00:34:44,680 --> 00:34:47,680
Let's give it up for our director!

539
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:51,599
Say something about the project.

540
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:52,600
Okay.

541
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,440
Thanks so much, everyone.

542
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:57,536
We'll be working together
for the next few months.

543
00:34:57,560 --> 00:35:00,920
It's going to be exhausting,
but I'm sure it'll turn out great.

544
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:05,440
And thank you, Arnold, for being my Romeo.

545
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:07,280
It took me forever to find the right one.

546
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:14,479
Thank you for having me, guys.

547
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:15,480
Clap!

548
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,120
And…

549
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,240
Thank you, Raffy,

550
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:26,960
for taking on that role for me.

551
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:36,840
I should be the one thanking you
for asking me to come back.

552
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:42,880
Come to think of it,
I might learn a lot from this project.

553
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:54,440
Let the others learn. Let us drink.

554
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,400
Hope it's a success!

555
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,160
Cheers!

556
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:07,520
We should play a game.

557
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:08,280
Name a province
I want in.

558
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:10,280
Come on.

559
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,319
Name a province that ends with “buri.”

560
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:13,120
That's easy.

561
00:36:13,121 --> 00:36:14,640
You go first.

562
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:16,400
Hey.

563
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:19,360
If you're too drunk to ride home,
you can crash here.

564
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,320
I'm not drunk yet.

565
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:24,040
You've been drinking a lot.

566
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:26,000
It's not safe to ride your bike.

567
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:28,120
Tua, don't worry.

568
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:31,159
I never ride when I'm drunk.

569
00:36:31,160 --> 00:36:32,760
If I go over my limit, I'll book a ride.

570
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:34,080
Okay?

571
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:35,896
I'm going to the bathroom.

572
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:36,920
Mm.

573
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:45,520
Asking him to stay over, huh?

574
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:48,560
Don't tease me.

575
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:52,000
Nice move.
Sneaking your crush into the project.

576
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:53,480
Dean.

577
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:55,640
Keep your voice down. People can hear.

578
00:36:59,880 --> 00:37:03,520
If you like him that much,
why don't you just tell him?

579
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:05,320
What are you afraid of?

580
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:08,640
If it were that simple,
I would've done it a long time ago.

581
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:13,160
But if you don't do anything,
how is this going to move forward?

582
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:21,440
Tell you what,
it's not that hard to create sparks.

583
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:24,200
You should try kissing him.

584
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:27,080
Huh? Kiss him?

585
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:29,600
Yeah, kiss him. Trust me.

586
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:33,600
No.

587
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:35,800
I'm not that bold.

588
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:37,560
I'm not you.

589
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:43,360
If he kisses you back,
it means he likes you too.

590
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:49,480
Build it up.

591
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:51,360
Your courage.

592
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:00,360
This is the best way.

593
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:02,000
So Tua can finally get a boyfriend.

594
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,440
Can I light my cigarette from yours?

595
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:18,560
Sure.

596
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:35,880
Hey.

597
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,440
Have you read the script?

598
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:39,640
Yeah, I have.

599
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:44,240
But honestly, I'm not
sure I can pull it off.

600
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:47,480
Oh, please. You need
to believe in yourself.

601
00:38:48,040 --> 00:38:49,480
I believe in you.

602
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,000
Mm.

603
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,160
I'll do my best.

604
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:58,280
To thank you for
rewriting the script for me.

605
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:33,000
What's the deal between you and Raffy?

606
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:36,960
The way you look at him,
it feels like more than just friends.

607
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:39,320
You into him?

608
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,240
Why do you care?

609
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,400
Just answer me.

610
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,400
He's kind of cute.

611
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:47,960
Teasable.

612
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:50,720
Even though he likes Jack?

613
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:53,280
Screw that.

614
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:54,440
Why?

615
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,000
Why does everyone like Jack?

616
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,040
What's so great about him?

617
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,560
Do you really want me to say it?

618
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:02,920
You two are back together?

619
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:04,600
Not yet.

620
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:06,280
But…

621
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:09,160
I don't want anyone else to have him.

622
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,120
Wow.

623
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,400
You're evil.

624
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:23,360
How about this, Rome?

625
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:26,560
Let me serve him up for you.

626
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:31,280
Whether you take him
or not, that's your call.

627
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,919
I really like the new script you wrote.

628
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,999
How did you even come up with that?

629
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:45,480
You made the character so well-rounded.

630
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:46,960
I'm glad you like it.

631
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:48,880
Jack.

632
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:55,920
Oh, hey.

633
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:58,400
That Past Lives poster you said you liked,

634
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:00,480
I finally got it for you.

635
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,800
Want to come and get it?

636
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,160
You can go get it and show me.

637
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:17,800
What's wrong?

638
00:41:18,040 --> 00:41:21,280
Are you afraid you won't be able to control
yourself like that night in your room?

639
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:27,960
Sorry.

640
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:29,520
It's an inside joke.

641
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:35,760
It's fine.

642
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:37,160
I don't mind.

643
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:42,520
What the fuck is wrong with Dean?

644
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,240
Acting all territorial over his ex.

645
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:47,960
Did you see his face?

646
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:04,160
What are you doing?

647
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,440
Why would you say that in front of Raffy?

648
00:42:08,440 --> 00:42:09,760
I don't like seeing him with you.

649
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:12,920
Keep this in mind.

650
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:17,920
You and I are never getting back together.

651
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:20,640
I didn't even do anything.

652
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:24,560
I don't mind if you
move on with someone else.

653
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:27,800
Just not Raffy.

654
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:30,760
Why?

655
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:33,160
Scared of losing?

656
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:35,920
I never lose.

657
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:39,360
But someone like me…

658
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:41,520
could make you lose.

659
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:05,760
But no one knows you better than I do.

660
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:10,440
Ouch!

661
00:44:12,560 --> 00:44:13,560
I told you.

662
00:44:14,040 --> 00:44:16,600
Someone like me can make you lose.

663
00:44:18,160 --> 00:44:21,080
As for the poster, I'll
transfer you the money.

664
00:44:44,346 --> 00:44:45,346
Oh, wow.

665
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:47,200
Look at you.

666
00:44:47,840 --> 00:44:49,000
Already drunk?

667
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:50,480
That was fast.

668
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:52,040
Just a little tipsy.

669
00:44:53,920 --> 00:44:56,520
Looks like everyone likes you.

670
00:44:57,240 --> 00:44:58,840
Guess you can relax now.

671
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:01,080
It's all thanks to you, Tua.

672
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:04,280
I don't usually have
friends outside my major.

673
00:45:04,640 --> 00:45:05,720
You're the only one.

674
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:07,160
So, thank you.

675
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:13,600
Let me get another drink.
I have to keep up with you.

676
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:24,520
Look.

677
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:27,600
About that kiss.

678
00:45:28,840 --> 00:45:29,840
Do you want to try?

679
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:32,520
Huh?

680
00:45:41,520 --> 00:45:42,960
Why don't you try that kiss with me?

681
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:47,160
If you're curious what
it's like to kiss a guy.

682
00:46:30,080 --> 00:46:31,080
So?

683
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:34,040
Feel anything?

684
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:47,480
I'm not sure yet.

685
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:50,200
Maybe it's because I'm drunk.

686
00:46:51,200 --> 00:46:55,200
I guess I'll know when I'm sober.

687
00:47:27,326 --> 00:47:28,446
Running off after you lost?

688
00:47:31,640 --> 00:47:34,240
It's normal for people with history
to end up in bed again, right?

689
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:37,640
None of your damn business.

690
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:40,920
They say constant dripping
wears away a stone.

691
00:47:42,160 --> 00:47:44,560
Too bad the stone you want won't budge.

692
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:47,720
And it's already claimed by someone else.

693
00:47:50,160 --> 00:47:51,160
Hold on.

694
00:47:52,920 --> 00:47:54,240
I think…

695
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:57,480
I'm top-tier myself.

696
00:47:59,200 --> 00:48:00,480
Whenever you want it…

697
00:48:07,160 --> 00:48:08,160
I'm always ready.

698
00:48:12,920 --> 00:48:17,160
If we do it one more
time, will you tell Jack?

699
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:22,440
Nope.

700
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:24,400
Why would I?

701
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:26,800
Something this delicious…

702
00:48:27,760 --> 00:48:29,080
I'd rather keep to myself.

703
00:49:17,360 --> 00:49:18,360
Cheers.

704
00:49:18,960 --> 00:49:19,960
Hey.

705
00:49:20,160 --> 00:49:21,400
Who's here at this hour?

706
00:49:21,520 --> 00:49:22,520
I'll get it.

707
00:49:33,080 --> 00:49:34,080
Hey!

708
00:49:35,080 --> 00:49:36,760
You're here, American boy?

709
00:49:37,520 --> 00:49:38,600
Am I too late?

710
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:40,160
No.

711
00:49:41,440 --> 00:49:43,400
Guys, this is my friend Boston.

712
00:49:43,920 --> 00:49:45,640
He's shooting our poster photos.

713
00:49:55,080 --> 00:49:56,400
Mind if I join your friend group?

714
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:08,416
(Next Episode)
What's up with you and Boston?

715
00:50:08,440 --> 00:50:09,600
Still mad about before?

716
00:50:09,720 --> 00:50:10,720
Why would I be?

717
00:50:10,920 --> 00:50:13,040
So you're not mad,
but it's still on your mind, right?

718
00:50:13,120 --> 00:50:15,760
If you see him again, give me a signal.
I can be your human shield.

719
00:50:17,480 --> 00:50:18,480
Can I tag along?

720
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:20,256
There are lots of secrets at this party.

721
00:50:20,280 --> 00:50:22,840
Whatever you see, don't tell anyone.

722
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,200
Poor thing.

723
00:50:24,320 --> 00:50:25,416
All you'll ever be is a supporting role.

724
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:26,440
Don't fall.

725
00:50:26,640 --> 00:50:27,640
Or I'll step on you.

726
00:50:30,280 --> 00:50:32,296
You didn't spread this around
because you were mad, right?

727
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:34,479
You have no right to question me
or be mad at me!

728
00:50:34,480 --> 00:50:35,240
Jack, you bastard!
Hey!

729
00:50:35,840 --> 00:50:36,840
What?
